==English==

===Etymology===
Named for [[w:Edmond Halley|Edmond Halley]], the English astronomer who first studied it.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˌhæli:z ˈkɒmɪt/, /ˌheɪli:z ˈkɒmɪt/}}

===Noun===
'''Halley's Comet'''
# A very bright [[comet]] which can be seen every 75-76 years.

